<p><b><a name="intraoral" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>There are several types of intraoral X-rays, each of which shows different
aspects of teeth.</p>.<p><b><a name="extraoral" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>There are several types of extraoral X-rays that your dentist may wish to
take.</p>.<p><b><a name="digital" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>There's a newer X-ray technique that your dentist already may be using or
may soon be using. It's called digital imaging. Instead of developing X-ray
film in a dark room, the X-rays are sent directly to a computer and can be
viewed on screen, stored, or printed out. There are several nice benefits of
using this new technology including:</p>.<p class="credits">Reviewed by the doctors at The Cleveland Clinic Department of Dentistry.<br><br>
